 Foreign accented characters corrupted!}+{\footnote \pard\plain \s16\nowidctlpar \f5\fs20\lang2057 {\cs17\super +} faq:08}} My non-English accented characters are corrupted!
\par \pard\plain \widctlpar \f5\fs20\lang2057 If you get a Refer file that contains accented characters these may not display properly.  The cause of this is that DOS-based programs do not use t
he same character codings as Windows.  Open the File, Import dialog box.  Select the Refer format and click the Options button.  In the dialog there is a checkbox for OEM to ANSI character conversion.  You should select this if you are reading files creat
ed by a non-Windows program, or when saving files for export to a non-Windows program.  The rest of the time you should leave it switched off;  the ANSI character set is rather better for accented characters, and having the conversion enabled slows {\i 
Refs} down when saving and loading files.
\par 
